obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (91715)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91715&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Telecommunications`
  line `Act, 2023.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to,--`
  line
  line `(i) the whole of India; and`
  line
  line `(ii) to any offence committed or contravention made outside India by any person, as provided in`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act and any`
  line `reference in any such provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to the`
  line `commencement of that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 26th June, 2024.--Sections 1,2,10 to 30, 42 to 44, 46, 47, 50 to 58, 61 and 62, vide Notification NO. S. O. 2408 (E), dated 26th June, 2024, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3 (ii).`
  line
  line `5th July, 2024.--Sections 6 to 8, 48 and 59(b), vide Notification No. S.O. 2623(E), dated the 5th July, 2024, see Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (91716)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91716&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "appointed day" means such date as the Central Government may, by notification appoint`
  line `under sub-section (3) of section 1;`
  line
  line `(b) "assignment" of a radio frequency or radio frequency channel means the permission for a`
  line `radio station to use a radio frequency or radio frequency channel under specified conditions;`
  line
  line `(c) "assignee" means a person holding an assignment of a radio frequency or radio frequency`
  line `channel under section 4;`
  line
  line `(d) "authorisation" means a permission, by whatever name called, granted under this Act for--`
  line
  line `(i) providing telecommunication services;`
  line
  line `(ii) establishing, operating, maintaining or expanding telecommunication networks; or`
  line
  line `(iii) possessing radio equipment;`
  line
  line `(e) "authorised entity" means a person holding an authorisation under section 3;`
  line
  line `(f) "critical telecommunication infrastructure" means telecommunication networks notified under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 22;`
  line
  line `(g) "message" means any sign, signal, writing, text, image, sound, video, data stream, intelligence`
  line `or information sent through telecommunication;`
  line
  line `(h) "National Frequency Allocation Plan" means guidelines issued from time to time by the`
  line `Central Government for the use of the spectrum;`
  line
  line `(i) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette and the expression`
  line `"notified" shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(j) "person" shall include an individual, any company or association or body of individuals,`
  line `whether incorporated or not, by whatsoever name called or referred to;`
  line
  line `(k) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(l) "radio equipment" means telecommunication equipment used or capable of use for`
  line `telecommunication by means of Hertzian or radio waves;`
  line
  line `(m) "radio waves" means electro-magnetic waves of frequencies propagated in space without any`
  line `artificial guide;`
  line
  line `(n) "Schedule" means a schedule to this Act;`
  line
  line `(o) "spectrum" means the range of frequencies of Hertzian or radio waves;`
  line
  line `(p) "telecommunication" means transmission, emission or reception of any messages, by wire,`
  line `radio, optical or other electro-magnetic systems, whether or not such messages have been subjected to`
  line `rearrangement, computation or other processes by any means in the course of their transmission,`
  line `emission or reception;`
  line
  line `(q) "telecommunication equipment" means any equipment, appliance, instrument, device, radio`
  line `station, radio equipment, material, apparatus, or user equipment, that may be or is being used for`
  line `telecommunication, including software and intelligence integral to such telecommunication`
  line `equipment; and excludes such equipment as may be notified by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(r) "telecommunication identifier" means a series of digits, characters and symbols, or a`
  line `combination thereof, used to identify uniquely a user, a telecommunication service, a`
  line `telecommunication network, elements of a telecommunication network, telecommunication`
  line `equipment, or an authorised entity;`
  line
  line `(s) "telecommunication network" means a system or series of systems of telecommunication`
  line `equipment or infrastructure, including terrestrial or satellite networks or submarine networks, or a`
  line `combination of such networks, used or intended to be used for providing telecommunication services,`
  line `but does not include such telecommunication equipment as notified by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(t) "telecommunication service" means any service for telecommunication;`
  line
  line `(u) "user"means a natural or legal person using or requesting a telecommunication service, but`
  line `does not include person providing such telecommunication service or telecommunication network.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (91717)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Authorisation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91717&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person intending to---`
  line
  line `(a) provide telecommunication services;`
  line
  line `(b) establish, operate, maintain or expand telecommunication network; or`
  line
  line `(c) possess radio equipment,`
  line
  line `shall obtain an authorisation from the Central Government, subject to such terms and conditions,`
  line `including fees or charges, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may while making rules under sub-section (1) provide for different`
  line `terms and conditions of authorisation for different types of telecommunication services,`
  line `telecommunication network or radio equipment.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government, if it determines that it is necessary in the public interest so to do, may`
  line `provide exemption from the requirement of authorisation under sub-section (1), in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(4) Any exemption granted prior to the appointed day under the Indian Telegraph`
  line `Act, 1885 (13 of 1885) or the Indian Wireless Telegraphy Act, 1933 (17 of 1933) shall continue under`
  line `this Act, unless otherwise notified by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) Any authorised entity may undertake any merger, demerger or acquisition, or other forms of`
  line `restructuring, subject to any law for the time being in force and any authorised entity that emerges`
  line `pursuant to such process, shall comply with the terms and conditions, including fees and charges,`
  line `applicable to the original authorised entity, and such other terms and conditions, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(6) A licence, registration, permission, by whatever name called, granted prior to the appointed day`
  line `under the Indian Telegraph Act, 1885 (13 of 1885) or the Indian Wireless Telegraphy`
  line `Act, 1933 (17 of 1933), in respect of provision of telecommunication services or telecommunication`
  line network---
  line
  line `(a) where a definite validity period is given, shall be entitled to continue to operate under the`
  line `terms and conditions and for the duration as specified under such licence or registration or`
  line `permission, or to migrate to such terms and conditions of the relevant authorisation, as may be`
  line `prescribed; or`
  line
  line `(b) where a definite validity period is not given, shall be entitled to continue to operate on the`
  line `terms and conditions of such licence or registration or permission for a period of five years from the`
  line `appointed day, or to migrate to such terms and conditions of the relevant authorisation, as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(7) Any authorised entity which provides such telecommunication services as may be notified by the`
  line `Central Government, shall identify the person to whom it provides telecommunication services through`
  line `use of any verifiable biometric based identification as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(8) The Central Government may, subject to such terms and conditions, including fees or charges as`
  line `may be prescribed, allot telecommunication identifiers for use by authorised entities.`
  line
  line `(9) The Central Government may allow use of telecommunication identifiers allotted by international`
  line `bodies which are recognised by the Central Government from time to time.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (91718)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Assignment of spectrum.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91718&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government, being the owner of the spectrum on`
  line `behalf of the people, shall assign the spectrum in accordance with this Act, and may notify a National`
  line `Frequency Allocation Plan from time to time.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person intending to use spectrum shall require an assignment from the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may prescribe such terms and conditions as may be applicable, for such`
  line `assignment of spectrum, including the frequency range, methodology for pricing, price, fees and charges,`
  line `payment mechanism, duration and procedure for the same.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall assign spectrum for telecommunication through auction except for`
  line `entries listed in the First Schedule for which assignment shall be done by administrative process.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this sub-section,—`
  line
  line `(a) “administrative process” means assignment of spectrum without holding an auction;`
  line
  line `(b) “auction” means a bid process for assignment of spectrum.`
  line
  line `(5) (a) The Central Government may, by notification, amend the First Schedule for assignment of`
  line spectrum—
  line
  line `(i) in order to serve public interest; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in order to perform government function; or`
  line
  line `(iii) in cases where auction of spectrum is not the preferred mode of assignment due to`
  line `technical or economic reasons.`
  line
  line `(b) The notification referred to in clause (a) shall be laid before each House of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(6) The Central Government, if it determines that it is necessary in the public interest so to do, may`
  line exempt,—
  line
  line `(a) from the requirement of assignment under sub-section (2), in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed; and`
  line
  line `(b) by notification, specific usages within specified frequencies and parameters, from the`
  line `requirements of sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(7) Any exemption with respect to use of spectrum granted under the Indian Telegraph`
  line `Act, 1885 (13 of 1885) and the Indian Wireless Telegraphy Act, 1933 (17 of 1933) prior to the appointed`
  line `day, shall continue under this Act, unless otherwise notified by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(8) Any spectrum assigned through the administrative process prior to the appointed day, shall`
  line `continue to be valid on the terms and conditions on which it had been assigned, for a period of five years`
  line `from the appointed day, or the date of expiry of such assignment, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(9) Any spectrum assigned through auction prior to the appointed day, shall continue to be valid on`
  line `the terms and conditions on which it had been assigned.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (91719)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Re-farming and harmonisation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91719&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, to enable more efficient use of`
  line `spectrum, re-farm or harmonise any frequency range assigned under section 4, subject to such terms and`
  line `conditions, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section,—`
  line
  line `(a) “harmonisation” means rearrangement of a frequency range;`
  line
  line `(b) “re-farming” means repurposing of a frequency range for a different use, other than that for`
  line `which it is used by an existing assignee.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (91720)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Technologically neutral use of spectrum.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91720&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may enable the utilisation`
  line `of the spectrum in a flexible, liberalised and technologically neutral manner, subject to such terms and`
  line `conditions, including applicable fees and charges, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (91721)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Optimal utilisation of spectrum.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91721&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, to promote optimal use of`
  line `the available spectrum, assign a particular part of a spectrum that has already been assigned to an entity,`
  line `known as the primary assignee, to one or more additional entities, known as the secondary assignees,`
  line `where such secondary assignment does not cause harmful interference in the use of the relevant part of`
  line `the spectrum by the primary assignee, subject to such terms and conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time`
  line `being in force, after providing a reasonable opportunity of being heard to the assignee concerned,`
  line `determines that any assigned spectrum has remained unutilised for insufficient reasons for such period as`
  line `may be prescribed, terminate such assignment, or a part of such assignment, or prescribe further terms`
  line `and conditions relating to spectrum utilisation.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (91722)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Establishment of monitoring and enforcement mechanism.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91722&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may`
  line `establish by notification, such monitoring and enforcement mechanism as it may deem fit to ensure`
  line `adherence to terms and conditions of spectrum utilisation and enable interference-free use of the assigned`
  line spectrum.
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may permit the sharing, trading, leasing and surrender of assigned`
  line `spectrum, subject to the terms and conditions, including applicable fees or charges, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (91723)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `No refund of fees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91723&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `No person shall be entitled to the refund of any fees or charges paid in respect`
  line `of or under an authorisation or assignment granted under this Act, if such authorisation or assignment is`
  line `suspended, curtailed, revoked or varied.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (91724)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Definition of terms used in this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91724&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of this Chapter,---`
  line
  line `(a) "facility provider" means the Central Government or any authorised entity, including any`
  line `contractor or sub-contractor or agent working for the Central Government or authorised entity, and`
  line `shall include their successor or assignee;`
  line
  line `(b) "public entity" means,---`
  line
  line `(i) the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(ii) the State Government;`
  line
  line `(iii) local authority;`
  line
  line `(iv) any authority, body, company or institution incorporated or established by the Central`
  line `Government or the State Government, or under any statute; or`
  line
  line `(v) any non-government entity vested with the ownership, control or management of any`
  line `public facility or class of public facilities, as may be notified by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(c) "public property" means any property, whether movable or immovable including any`
  line `machinery, which is owned by, or in the possession of, or under the control or management of any`
  line `public entity.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (91725)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Right of way for telecommunication network in public property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91725&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any facility provider`
  line `may submit an application to a public entity under whose ownership, control or management, the public`
  line `property is vested, to seek permissions for right of way for telecommunication network under, over,`
  line `along, across, in or upon such public property.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of an application from a facility provider under sub-section (1), the public entity shall,`
  line `subject to the provisions of sub-section (4), grant permission for all or any of the following acts,`
  line `namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) survey such property for the purpose of assessing the feasibility for establishing`
  line `telecommunication network; or`
  line
  line `(b) enter the property from time to time to establish, operate, maintain, repair, replace, augment,`
  line `remove or relocate any telecommunication network.`
  line
  line `(3) The public entity shall grant permission under sub-section (2) in an expeditious manner and within`
  line `such timelines as may be prescribed, and subject to such administrative expenses and compensation for`
  line `right of way, which shall not exceed such amount as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) Any rejection of an application under sub-section (1) shall be based on reasonable grounds to be`
  line `recorded in writing.`
  line
  line `(5) The facility provider shall do as little damage as possible to the public property, and ensure that`
  line `the functionality and continuity of operations over such public property is not adversely affected, while`
  line `undertaking any of the activities for which permission has been granted under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(6) If any damage is caused to the property, the facility provider shall, at the option of the public`
  line `entity, either,---`
  line
  line `(a) restore such property to its state as existed prior to the undertaking of such activities; or`
  line
  line `(b) pay compensation for such damage as may be mutually agreed.`
  line
  line `(7) The provisions of this section shall be applicable to any public property vested for such projects or`
  line `class of projects as notified by the Central Government, in respect of which, applications under`
  line `sub-section (1) shall be made to the public entity granting the concession, contract or permission for such`
  line projects.
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (91726)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Right of way for telecommunication network on property not covered under section 11.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91726&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any facility provider may submit an application to the person under whose ownership,`
  line `control or management of property not covered under section 11 is vested, to seek right of way for`
  line `telecommunication network under, over, along, across, in or upon such property.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of an application from a facility provider, the person receiving the application may`
  line `enter into an agreement, specifying consideration as mutually agreed, for---`
  line
  line `(a) undertaking surveys as may be required by the facility provider for the purpose of assessing`
  line `the feasibility for establishing telecommunication network; or`
  line
  line `(b) establishing, operating, maintaining, repairing, replacing, augmenting, removing or relocating`
  line `any telecommunication network by the facility provider.`
  line
  line `(3) The facility provider shall do as little damage as possible to the property when undertaking any of`
  line `the activities for which permission has been granted under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) In case of any damage to the property, the facility provider shall restore such property to its state`
  line `as existed prior to the undertaking of such activities, failing which the person granting permission under`
  line `sub-section (2), shall be entitled to compensation as may be mutually agreed, for any such damage.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government may by rules provide for the procedure to be followed by a facility`
  line `provider to enter, survey, establish, operate, maintain, repair, replace or relocate the telecommunication`
  line `network, including the notice period, the manner of issuance of notice, the framework governing`
  line `objections by owner or occupier of the property, the manner in which such objections would be resolved,`
  line `and matters relating to the compensation payable for any damage.`
  line
  line `(6) If the person under sub-section (2) fails to provide the right of way requested, and the Central`
  line `Government determines that it is necessary so to do in the public interest, it may, either by itself or`
  line `through any other authority designated by the Central Government for this purpose, determine that such`
  line `facility provider shall be permitted the right of way to establish, operate, maintain such`
  line `telecommunication network, subject to such terms and conditions, including charges for the right of way,`
  line `and compensation for damage to the property, if any, to be payable to such person as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (91727)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Non-discriminatory and non- exclusive grant of right of way.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91727&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Any person providing right of`
  line `way under section 11 or section 12, shall ensure grant of right of way to the facility providers in a`
  line `non-discriminatory manner and, as far as practicable, on a non-exclusive basis.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (91728)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Telecommunication network distinct from property on which it is installed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91728&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) A facility`
  line `provider shall not have any right, title or interest in the property on which telecommunication network is`
  line `established, except the right to use the property as provided under section 11 or section 12.`
  line
  line `(2) The telecommunication network installed on any property, shall not be subject to any claims,`
  line `encumbrances, liquidation or the like, relating to such property.`
  line
  line `(3) The telecommunication network installed on any property, shall not be considered as part of such`
  line `property, including for the purposes of any transaction related to that property, or any property tax, levy,`
  line `cess, fees or duties as may be applicable on that property.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, no public entity,`
  line `except with the permission of an officer authorised by the Central Government for this purpose, shall`
  line `have the authority to take any coercive action, such as sealing, preventing access, or forcible shutdown of`
  line `the telecommunication network established by an authorised enttity, except where such actions may be`
  line `necessary to deal with any natural disaster or public emergency.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (91729)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Power of Central Government to establish common ducts and cable corridors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91729&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Central Government may notify infrastructure projects or class of infrastructure projects, whether being`
  line `developed by a public entity by itself, through a public private partnership or by any other person, that`
  line `may require establishment of common ducts or conduits or cable corridors, for installation of`
  line `telecommunication network..`
  line
  line `(2) The telecommunication network referred to in sub-section (1) shall be made available on open`
  line `access basis to facility providers, subject to such terms and conditions, including fees and charges, as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (91730)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Removal, relocation or alteration of telecommunication network.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91730&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, under`
  line `section 11 or section 12, telecommunication network has been placed by the facility provider, under, over,`
  line `along, across, in or upon any property, and any person entitled to do so desires to deal with that property`
  line `in such a manner so as to render it necessary or convenient that the telecommunication network should be`
  line `removed or relocated to another part thereof or to a higher or lower level or altered in form, he may`
  line `require the facility provider to remove, relocate or alter the telecommunication network accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) If compensation has been paid under sub-section (6) of section 11, or sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 12, such person shall, when making the requisition under sub-section (1), tender to the facility`
  line `provider the amount requisite to defray the expense of the removal, relocation or alteration on such terms`
  line `as may be mutually agreed.`
  line
  line `(3) If any dispute arises under this Chapter, the matter shall be determined by the authority referred to`
  line `in sub-section (2) of section 18.`
  line
  line `(4) If the facility provider omits to comply with the requisition, the person making such requisition,`
  line `may apply to the District Magistrate within whose jurisdiction the property is situated, to order the`
  line `relocation or alteration.`
  line
  line `(5) The District Magistrate receiving the application may, at its discretion and for reasons to be`
  line `recorded in writing, approve or reject such relocation or alteration, subject to such conditions as it`
  line `determines fit, including the relocation of the telecommunication network to any other part of the property`
  line `or to a higher or lower level or for the alteration of its form, and the order so made shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (91731)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Notice to facility provider.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91731&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person desiring to exercise his right to deal with his`
  line `property in such a manner as is likely to cause damage or to interrupt or interfere with the`
  line `telecommunication network established under the provisions of this Act, or to interrupt or interfere with`
  line `telecommunication services, shall give prior notice of such duration and in such manner, as may be`
  line `prescribed, to the facility provider, the Central Government or to any authority that may be notified by the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The facility provider shall respond to such notice with details of such telecommunication network`
  line `and precautionary measures to be undertaken, within such timelines as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a person referred to in sub-section (1) gives a notice of his exercise of the right relating to`
  line `his property with the bona fide intention of averting imminent danger of personal injury to himself or any`
  line `other person, such person shall be deemed to have complied with the provisions of the said sub-section.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person who fails to comply with the provisions of sub-section (1), or deals with any property`
  line `in such a manner as is likely to cause, or causes, damage to any telecommunication network, or is likely`
  line `to interrupt or interfere, or interrupts or interferes with telecommunication services, a District Magistrate`
  line `may, on the application of the facility provider, order such person to abstain from dealing with such`
  line `property in such manner for a period not exceeding one month from the date of his order and forthwith to`
  line `take such action with regard to such property as may be in the opinion of the District Magistrate necessary`
  line `to remedy or prevent such damage, interruption or interference during such period.`
  line
  line `(5) If any dispute arises relating to damages, the matter shall be determined by the authority referred`
  line `to under sub-section (2) of section 18.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (91732)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Dispute resolution relating to this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91732&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The District Magistrate, or any other`
  line `authority as notified by the Central Government, within whose jurisdiction the property is situated, shall`
  line `have the exclusive powers to resolve any disputes under this Chapter, except for disputes referred to`
  line `under sub-section (2) of this section.`
  line
  line `(2) If any dispute arises relating to compensation under sub-section (6) of section 11, sub-section (2)`
  line `and sub-section (4) of section 12, and sub-section (5) of section 17, it shall, on an application made for`
  line `that purpose by either of the disputing parties to the District Judge within whose jurisdiction the property`
  line `is situated, be determined by him.`
  line
  line `(3) Every determination of a dispute by a District Magistrate or District Judge under this section, shall`
  line `be final.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in sub-section (3) shall affect the right of any person to recover by suit the whole or any`
  line `part of any compensation paid by the facility provider, from the person who has received the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (91733)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Power to notify standards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91733&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may notify standards and conformity`
  line `assessment measures in respect of—.`
  line
  line `(a) telecommunication equipment, telecommunication identifiers and telecommunication`
  line network;.
  line
  line `(b) telecommunication services, in consonance with any regulations notified by the Telecom`
  line `Regulatory Authority of India from time to time;.`
  line
  line `(c) manufacture, import, distribution and sale of telecommunication equipment;.`
  line
  line `(d) telecommunication security, including identification, analysis and prevention of intrusion in`
  line `telecommunication services and telecommunication networks;.`
  line
  line `(e) cyber security for telecommunication services and telecommunication networks; and.`
  line
  line `(f) encryption and data processing in telecommunication.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (91734)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Provisions for public emergency or public safety.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91734&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the occurrence of any public`
  line `emergency, including disaster management, or in the interest of public safety, the Central Government or`
  line `a State Government or any officer specially authorised in this behalf by the Central Government or a State`
  line `Government, if satisfied that it is necessary or expedient so to do, by notification—`
  line
  line `(a) take temporary possession of any telecommunication service or telecommunication network`
  line `from an authorised entity; or`
  line
  line `(b) provide for appropriate mechanism to ensure that messages of a user or group of users`
  line `authorised for response and recovery during public emergency are routed on priority.`
  line
  line `(2) On the occurrence of any public emergency or in the interest of public safety, the Central`
  line `Government or a State Government or any officer specially authorised in this behalf by the Central`
  line `Government or a State Government, may, if satisfied that it is necessary or expedient so to do, in the`
  line `interest of the sovereignty and integrity of India, defence and security of the State, friendly relations with`
  line `foreign States, public order, or for preventing incitement to the commission of any offence, subject to`
  line `such procedure and safeguards as may be prescribed, and for reasons to be recorded in writing, by`
  line order—
  line
  line `(a) direct that any message or class of messages, to or from any person or class of persons, to or`
  line `from any telecommunication equipment or class of telecommunication equipment, or relating to any`
  line `particular subject, brought for transmission by, or transmitted or received by any telecommunication`
  line `service or telecommunication network, shall not be transmitted, or shall be intercepted or detained, or`
  line `shall be disclosed in intelligible format to the officer mentioned in such order; or`
  line
  line `(b) direct that any telecommunication service or class of telecommunication services to or from`
  line `any person or class of persons, to or from any telecommunication equipment or class of`
  line `telecommunication equipment, or relating to any particular subject, transmitted or received by any`
  line `telecommunication service or telecommunication network, shall be suspended.`
  line
  line `(3) The press messages, intended to be published in India, of correspondents accredited to the Central`
  line `Government or a State Government shall not be intercepted or detained, unless their transmission has`
  line `been prohibited under clause (a) of sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) The action specified under sub-section (1), sub-section (2) and sub-section (3) shall be for such`
  line `duration and in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (91735)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Measures for national security, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91735&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, if satisfied that it is`
  line `necessary or expedient so to do, in the interest of national security, friendly relations with foreign States,`
  line `or in the event of war, by notification take such measures as are necessary in the circumstances of the`
  line `case, including issuing directions in respect of the following, namely:—.`
  line
  line `(a) use of telecommunication equipment, telecommunication services, telecommunication`
  line `network and telecommunication identifiers;.`
  line
  line `(b) standards applicable to manufacture, import and distribution of telecommunication`
  line equipment;.
  line
  line `(c) standards to be adopted by authorised entities or assignees;.`
  line
  line `(d) procurement of telecommunication equipment and telecommunication services only from`
  line `trusted sources;.`
  line
  line `(e) suspension, removal or prohibition of the use of specified telecommunication equipment and`
  line `telecommunication services from countries or person as may be notified; or.`
  line
  line `(f) taking over the control and management of, or suspending the operation of, or entrusting any`
  line `authority of the Central Government to manage any or all of any telecommunication services, or any`
  line `telecommunication network or part thereof, connected with such telecommunication services.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (91736)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Protection of telecommunication network and telecommunication services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91736&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government may by rules provide for the measures to protect and ensure cyber security of`
  line `telecommunication networks and telecommunication services..`
  line
  line `(2) The measures may include collection, analysis and dissemination of traffic data that is generated,`
  line `transmitted, received or stored in telecommunication networks..`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression "traffic data" means any data`
  line `generated, transmitted, received or stored in telecommunication networks including data relating to the`
  line `type, routing, duration or time of a telecommunication..`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare any`
  line `telecommunication network, or part thereof, as Critical Telecommunication Infrastructure, disruption of`
  line `which shall have debilitating impact on national security, economy, public health or safety..`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may by rules provide for the standards, security practices, upgradation`
  line `requirements and procedures to be implemented for such Critical Telecommunication Infrastructure.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (91737)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Power to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91737&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `If it appears necessary or expedient so to do in the public interest, the`
  line `Central Government may direct any authorised entity to transmit in its telecommunication services or`
  line `telecommunication network, specific messages, in such manner as may be specified.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (91738)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Establishment of Digital Bharat Nidhi.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91738&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Universal Service Obligation Fund created`
  line `under the Indian Telegraph Act, 1885 (13 of 1885), shall, from the appointed day, be the “Digital Bharat`
  line `Nidhi”, under the control of the Central Government, and shall be used to discharge functions as set forth`
  line `in this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Any sums of money attributable to the Digital Bharat Nidhi that is paid pursuant to an`
  line `authorisation under section 3, shall be credited to the Digital Bharat Nidhi.`
  line
  line `(3) The balance to the credit of the Digital Bharat Nidhi shall not lapse at the end of the financial`
  line year.
  line
  line `(4) All amounts payable under licences granted prior to the appointed day towards the Universal`
  line `Service Obligation, shall be deemed to be the amounts payable towards the Digital Bharat Nidhi.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (91739)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Crediting of sum to Consolidated Fund of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91739&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `The sums of money received towards the`
  line `Digital Bharat Nidhi under section 24, shall first be credited to the Consolidated Fund of India, and the`
  line `Central Government may, if Parliament by appropriation made by law in this behalf so provides, credit`
  line `such proceeds to the Digital Bharat Nidhi from time to time for being utilised exclusively to meet any or`
  line `all of the following objectives, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) support universal service through promoting access to and delivery of telecommunication`
  line `services in underserved rural, remote and urban areas;`
  line
  line `(b) support research and development of telecommunication services, technologies, and products;`
  line
  line `(c) support pilot projects, consultancy assistance and advisory support towards provision of`
  line `service under clause (a) of this section;`
  line
  line `(d) support introduction of telecommunication services, technologies, and products.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (91740)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Administration of Digital Bharat Nidhi.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91740&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `The Digital Bharat Nidhi shall be administered in a`
  line `manner, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (91741)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Regulatory sandbox.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91741&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, for the purposes of encouraging and`
  line `facilitating innovation and technological development in telecommunication, create one or more`
  line `regulatory sandboxes, in such manner, and for such duration, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this section, the expression "regulatory sandbox" refers to a live`
  line `testing environment where new products, services, processes and business models which may be`
  line `deployed, on a limited set of users, for a specified period of time, with certain relaxations from the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (91742)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Measures for users.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91742&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of this section, specified message means any`
  line `message offering, advertising or promoting goods, services, interest in property, business opportunity,`
  line `employment opportunity or investment opportunity, whether or not---`
  line
  line `(a) the goods, services, interest, or opportunity are real; or`
  line
  line `(b) it is lawful to acquire such goods, services, property, interest or take up the opportunity.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may by rules provide for measures for protection of users, in consonance`
  line `with any regulations notified by the Telecom Regulatory Authority of India from time to time, including`
  line `measures such as---`
  line
  line `(a) the prior consent of users for receiving certain specified messages or class of specified`
  line messages;
  line
  line `(b) the preparation and maintenance of one or more registers, to be called as "Do Not Disturb"`
  line `register, to ensure that users do not receive specified messages or class of specified messages without`
  line `prior consent; or`
  line
  line `(c) the mechanism to enable users to report any malware or specified messages received in`
  line `contravention of this section.`
  line
  line `(3) An authorised entity providing telecommunication services shall establish an online mechanism to`
  line `enable users to register any grievance pertaining to the telecommunication service, and redressal of such`
  line `grievances, in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (91743)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Duty of users.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91743&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `No user shall—`
  line
  line `(a) furnish any false particulars, suppress any material information, or impersonate another`
  line `person, while establishing his identity for availing of telecommunication services; or`
  line
  line `(b) fail to share information as required under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (91744)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Dispute resolution mechanism to redress user grievances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91744&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may`
  line `establish or approve one or more online dispute resolution mechanisms for the resolution of disputes`
  line `between users and authorised entities providing telecommunication services.`
  line
  line `(2) Every authorised entity providing telecommunication services shall participate in the dispute`
  line `resolution mechanism established under sub-section (1), and shall comply with such terms and conditions`
  line `of participation in such mechanism as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) This section shall not affect the rights of consumers under the Consumer Protection Act, 2019`
  line `(35 of 2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (91745)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Definitions of terms used in this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91745&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of this Chapter,—`
  line
  line `(a) “Adjudicating Officer” means an officer appointed under section 35; and`
  line
  line `(b) “Designated Appeals Committee” means the committee appointed under section 36.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (91746)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Breach of terms and conditions of authorisation or assignment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91746&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) In case of breach of any`
  line `of the terms and conditions of authorisation or assignment granted under this Act, the Adjudicating`
  line `Officer shall, pursuant to an inquiry under the provisions of this Chapter—`
  line
  line `(a) pass an order in writing in respect of one or both of the following, namely: —`
  line
  line `(i) direct such authorised entity, or assignee to do or abstain from doing any act or thing to`
  line `prevent such breach or for such compliance;`
  line
  line `(ii) impose civil penalties as specified in the Second Schedule; and`
  line
  line `(b) make recommendations for the consideration of the Central Government regarding`
  line `suspension, revocation, or curtailment of the duration of the authorisation or assignment.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, after due consideration of the recommendations of the`
  line `Adjudicating Officer under clause (b) of sub-section (1), suspend, curtail or revoke the authorisation or`
  line `assignment, as the case may be, which may be reversed if the substantial violation is remedied to the`
  line `satisfaction of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) While imposing penalties specified in the Second Schedule under this section and section 33, the`
  line `Adjudicating Officer shall have due regard to the following factors, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) nature, gravity and duration of the contravention, taking into account the scope of the`
  line contravention;
  line
  line `(b) number of persons affected by such contravention, and the level of harm suffered by them;`
  line
  line `(c) intentional or negligent character of the contravention;`
  line
  line `(d) repetitive nature of the contravention;`
  line
  line `(e) action taken by the concerned person to mitigate the contravention, including by providing a`
  line `voluntary undertaking under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) of section 34;`
  line
  line `(f) revenue loss caused to the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(g) any aggravating factors relevant to the circumstances of the case, such as the amount of`
  line `disproportionate gain or unfair advantage, wherever quantifiable, made as a result of the`
  line `contravention; and`
  line
  line `(h) any mitigating factors relevant to the circumstances of the case, such as the timely`
  line `rectification of the contravention, or steps taken for the avoidance of loss as a result of the`
  line contravention.
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (91747)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Contraventions of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91747&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Adjudicating Officer shall, upon receipt of a complaint in such`
  line `form, manner and accompanied by such fees as may be prescribed, relating to contravention of this Act as`
  line `specified in the Third Schedule, or suo motu, conduct an inquiry under the provisions of this Chapter,`
  line `pass an order in writing specifying the civil penalty up to an amount as specified in the Third Schedule,`
  line `payable by the person committing such contravention.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of the Third Schedule shall apply to the abetment of, or attempt to commit, or`
  line `conspiracy to commit such contravention, as they apply to such contravention.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (91748)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Voluntary undertaking for contraventions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91748&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any authorised entity or assignee committing`
  line `the contravention as provided under section 32 or under serial No. 4 of the Third Schedule may, prior to`
  line `any notice or initiation of process of determination of such contravention, submit a voluntary undertaking`
  line `to the Adjudicating Officer, disclosing such contravention and measures taken or to be taken to mitigate`
  line `such contravention.`
  line
  line `(2) The acceptance of voluntary undertaking given under sub-section (1), subject to the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (6), shall constitute a bar on proceedings under this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Adjudicating Officer has reasonable grounds to believe that a contravention as`
  line `provided under section 32 or under serial No. 4 of the Third Schedule may have occurred, then it shall`
  line `serve a notice to the authorised entity or assignee concerned under the relevant section.`
  line
  line `(4) At any time during the process of hearing under sub-section (3), the authorised entity or assignee,`
  line `may, submit a voluntary undertaking specifying the mitigation measures it proposes to take in respect of`
  line `such contravention.`
  line
  line `(5) The acceptance of the voluntary undertaking submitted under sub-section (4), subject to the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (6), shall be construed as a mitigation measure and shall be duly considered for`
  line `the purpose of determination of civil penalties under clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 32, or under`
  line `serial No. 4 of the Third Schedule.`
  line
  line `(6) The voluntary undertaking under sub-section (1) or sub-section (4) of this section, may include an`
  line `undertaking to take a specified action within a specified time; an undertaking to refrain from taking a`
  line `specified action; and an undertaking to publicise the voluntary undertaking.`
  line
  line `(7) The Adjudicating Officer may accept the voluntary undertaking under sub-section (1) or`
  line `sub-section (4), or with the agreement of the authorised entity or assignee providing the voluntary`
  line `undertaking, vary the terms included in such voluntary undertaking.`
  line
  line `(8) When the authorised entity or assignee providing a voluntary undertaking fails to comply with any`
  line `terms of such undertaking, the Adjudicating Officer may, after giving such authorised entity or assignee a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard, proceed with imposition of civil penalties specified under the`
  line `Second Schedule or the Third Schedule, as applicable.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (91749)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Adjudicating Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91749&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of this Chapter, the Central Government shall, by`
  line `an order published in the Official Gazette, appoint any officer of the Central Government not below the`
  line `rank of Joint Secretary as one or more Adjudicating Officers for holding an inquiry in such manner as`
  line `may be prescribed..`
  line
  line `(2) The Adjudicating Officer may, upon the holding of such inquiry, pass such order as he deems fit`
  line `in accordance with the provisions of section 32 or section 33.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (91750)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Designated Appeals Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91750&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by an order published in`
  line `the Official Gazette, appoint officers of the Central Government not below the rank of Additional`
  line `Secretary, as members of one or more Designated Appeals Committee to which any person aggrieved by`
  line `an order made by the Adjudicating Officer under sub-section (1) of section 32 or under section 33, may`
  line `prefer an appeal.`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal under sub-section (1) shall be filed within a period of thirty days from the date on`
  line `which the copy of the order made by the Adjudicating Officer is received by the aggrieved person, and`
  line `shall be in such form, manner and be accompanied by such fees as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (91751)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Process to be followed by Adjudicating Officer and Designated Appeals Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91751&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `The functioning of the Adjudicating Officer and the Designated Appeals Committee shall, as far as`
  line `possible, be digital by design and they shall function as digital offices and deploy such techno-legal`
  line `measures as may be prescribed, to enable online process for their functioning.`
  line
  line `(2) The Adjudicating Officer and Designated Appeals Committee shall have the same powers as a`
  line `civil court, and all proceedings before it shall be deemed to be judicial proceedings within the meaning`
  line `of section 193 and 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (91752)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title Enforcement.
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91752&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `Any order made by the Adjudicating Officer or the Designated Appeals`
  line `Committee shall be executable in the same manner as if it were a decree of civil court; and such orders`
  line `shall be deemed to be final decrees under this section on the expiry of the period allowed for preferring an`
  line `appeal against such orders as provided in section 36 and section 39.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (91753)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Appeals on matters relating to section 32.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91753&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `Any person aggrieved by an order of the`
  line `Designated Appeals Committee under section 36, in so far as it pertains to matters under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 32, or an order of the Central Government under sub-section (2) of section 32, may prefer an`
  line `appeal to the Telecom Disputes Settlement and Appellate Tribunal constituted under section 14 of the`
  line `Telecom Regulatory Authority of India Act, 1997 (24 of 1997), within a period of thirty days from the`
  line `date on which a copy of the order is received by such authorised entity or assignee.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (91754)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Appeals on matters relating to section 33.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91754&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Any person aggrieved by an order of the`
  line `Designated Appeals Committee under section 36, in so far as it pertains to matters under section 33, may`
  line `prefer an appeal to any civil court having jurisdiction over the matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (91755)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Jurisdiction of civil court barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91755&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `No civil court shall have jurisdiction in respect of any`
  line `matter which the Adjudicating Officer, the Designated Appeals Committee, the Central Government or`
  line `the Telecom Disputes Settlement and Appellate Tribunal are empowered by or under this Chapter to`
  line determine.
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (91756)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `General provisions relating to offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91756&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever provides telecommunication services or`
  line `establishes telecommunication network without authorisation under sub-section (1) of section 3, or causes`
  line `damage to critical telecommunication infrastructure shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to three years, or with fine which may extend up to two crore rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever directly or indirectly or through personation---`
  line
  line `(a) gains or attempts to gain unauthorised access to a telecommunication network or to data of an`
  line `authorised entity or transfers data of an authorised entity; or`
  line
  line `(b) intercepts a message unlawfully,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years, or with fine which`
  line `may extend up to two crore rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this sub-section,---`
  line
  line `(i) the expression "personation" sha1ll have the same meaning as assigned to it under section`
  line `416 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860);`
  line
  line `(ii) data of an authorised entity includes call data records, internet protocol data records, traffic`
  line `data, subscriber data records and the like.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever, ---`
  line
  line `(a) possesses or uses without an authorisation, any equipment that blocks telecommunication;`
  line
  line `(b) uses telecommunication identifiers not allotted or permitted in accordance with`
  line `sub-sections (8) and (9) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) tampers with telecommunication identifiers;`
  line
  line `(d) possesses radio equipment without an authorisation or an exemption that can accommodate`
  line `more than specified number of subscriber identity modules;`
  line
  line `(e) obtains subscriber identity modules or other telecommunication identifiers through fraud,`
  line `cheating or personation;`
  line
  line `(f) wilfully possesses radio equipment knowing that it uses unauthorised or tampered`
  line `telecommunication identifiers,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years, or with fine which`
  line `may extend up to fifty lakh rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(4) Whoever wilfully contravenes any measures specified in the notification on national security`
  line `under section 21 shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years, or`
  line `with fine which may extend up to two crore rupees, or with both and the Central Government may, if it`
  line `deems fit, also suspend or terminate the telecommunication service of such person.`
  line
  line `(5) Whoever causes damage to telecommunication network, other than critical telecommunication`
  line `infrastructure shall be liable for compensation for the damage caused and fine which may extend up to`
  line `fifty lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(6) Whoever abets any offence, or attempts to commit, or conspires to commit an offence under this`
  line `Act, shall if the act abetted or conspired is committed in consequence of such abetment or conspiracy, be`
  line `punished with the punishment provided for the offence.`
  line
  line `(7) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), all`
  line `offences specified under this section shall be cognizable and non-bailable.`
  line
  line `(8) No court inferior to that of a Chief Metropolitan Magistrate or a Chief Judicial Magistrate of first`
  line `class shall try any offence punishable under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (91757)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Power to search.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91757&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `Any officer authorised by the Central Government in this behalf, may search`
  line `any building, vehicle, vessel, aircraft or place in which he has reason to believe that any unauthorised`
  line `telecommunication network or telecommunication equipment or radio equipment in respect of which an`
  line `offence punishable under section 42 has been committed, is kept or concealed and take possession`
  line thereof.
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (91758)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Supply of information to authorised officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91758&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any law`
  line `for the time being in force, where the Central Government is satisfied that any information, document or`
  line `record in possession or control of any authorised entity or assignee relating to any telecommunication`
  line `service, telecommunication network or use of spectrum, availed by any entity or consumer or subscriber`
  line `is necessary to be furnished in relation to any pending or apprehended civil or criminal proceedings, an`
  line `officer, specially authorised in writing by the Central Government in this behalf, shall direct such`
  line `authorised entity or assignee to furnish such information, document or record to him and the authorised`
  line `entity or assignee shall comply with the direction of such officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (91759)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Creation of security interests.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91759&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may provide for such security interest`
  line `which an authorised entity may provide to lenders financing such entities on such terms and conditions of`
  line `such security interest as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (91760)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Certification of person for operation of radio equipment on a vessel or aircraft.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91760&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line The
  line `Central Government may grant certification to any person to operate a radio equipment on such class of`
  line `vessels registered under the Merchant Shipping Act, 1958 (44 of 1958), aircrafts registered under the`
  line `Aircraft Act, 1934 (22 of 1934) and any other category of vessels or vehicles as may be notified by the`
  line `Central Government, in accordance with such terms and conditions, including applicable fees and`
  line `charges, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (91761)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Certification for amateur station operator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91761&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may by rules provide for`
  line `the manner of certification of person to install and operate an amateur station and such rules may specify`
  line `the qualifications and terms and conditions subject to which, a certification for operating an amateur`
  line `station may be granted, including through conduct of examinations for granting such certification, the fees`
  line `and charges to be paid thereof, and other connected matters.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section,`
  line
  line `(a) “amateur services” means radio communication services for the purpose of self-training,`
  line `intercommunication and technical investigations carried out by amateurs, that is, by duly`
  line `authorised person interested in radio technique solely with a personal aim and without any`
  line `pecuniary interest;`
  line
  line `(b) “amateur station” means a radio station operated by an amateur for amateur services.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (91762)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Prohibition of use of equipment which blocks telecommunication.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91762&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `No person shall possess`
  line `or use any equipment that blocks telecommunication unless permitted by the Central Government, or any`
  line `authority authorised for specific purpose by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (91763)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Penalties not to affect other liabilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91763&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) The penalties imposed pursuant to the provisions`
  line `of Chapter VIII or Chapter IX, shall be in addition to, and not in derogation of, any liability in respect of`
  line `payment of compensation or payment of any fees or charges due by an authorised entity or assignee.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of this Act are in addition to and without prejudice to any other liability which a`
  line `person may have incurred under any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (91764)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Act to apply for offence or contravention committed outside India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91764&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `This Act shall apply to`
  line `any offence committed or contravention made outside India by any person if the act or conduct`
  line `constituting such offence or contravention involves a telecommunication service provided in India, or`
  line `telecommunication equipment or telecommunication network located in India.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (91765)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91765&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government, the State Government, or any other authority under this Act or any`
  line `person acting on their behalf, as the case may be, for anything which is done in good faith, or intended to`
  line `be done in pursuance of this Act or any rule, regulation or order made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (91766)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Consistency with other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91766&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of this Act shall be in addition to, and not be`
  line `construed in derogation of the provisions of any other law, and shall be construed as consistent with such`
  line `law, for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(2) If any conflict arises between a provision of this Act and a provision of any other law for the time`
  line `being in force in the whole of India or restricted to the application within the territory of any State, the`
  line `provision of this Act shall prevail to the extent of such conflict.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (91767)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Implementation of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91767&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `The implementation of the Act shall be digital by design and the`
  line `Central Government shall take any such measures as necessary to enable the digital implementation of the`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (91768)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Employee of authorised entity not to be compelled to appear as witness.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91768&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `No employee of an`
  line `authorised entity shall, in any legal proceeding to which such authorised entity is not a party, be`
  line `compelled to appear as a witness to prove the information contained in any electronic records submitted under sub-section (4) of section 65B of the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872), except as required by`
  line `order of the Court or a Judge made for special cause.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (91769)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Rights in Continental Shelf and Exclusive Economic Zone.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91769&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `The privilege of the Central`
  line `Government to grant authorisations or assignment under this Act in the Continental Shelf and the`
  line `Exclusive Economic Zone of India and the rights of an authorised entity or assignee, as the case may be,`
  line `shall be subject to the Territorial Waters, Continental Shelf, Exclusive Economic Zone and other`
  line `Maritime Zones Act, 1976 (80 of 1976), and applicable international laws as accepted and ratified by`
  line India.
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (91770)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91770&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, and subject to the condition of previous publication, make rules not inconsistent with the`
  line `provisions of this Act, to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the terms and conditions, including fees or charges for obtaining authorisation under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner of exemption for providing authorisation under sub-section (3) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) the terms and conditions, including fees and charges, applicable to the original authorised`
  line `entity that emerges pursuant to any merger, demerger, acquisition, or other forms of restructuring,`
  line `under sub-section (5) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(d) the terms and conditions for migration under sub-section (6) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(e) the verifiable biometric based identification to be used by an authorised entity of`
  line `telecommunication services under sub-section (7) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(f) the terms and conditions, including fees or charges for allotment of telecommunication`
  line `identifiers for use by authorised entities under sub-section (8) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(g) the terms and conditions for the assignment of spectrum, including the frequency range,`
  line `methodology for pricing, price, fees and charges, payment mechanism, duration and procedure under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(h) the manner of exemptions for assignment of spectrum under sub-section (7) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(i) the terms and conditions for re-farming and harmonisation under section 5;`
  line
  line `(j) the terms and conditions, including applicable fees and charges, and any other relevant`
  line `condition subject to which the utilisation of the spectrum in a flexible, liberalised and technologically`
  line `neutral manner under section 6;`
  line
  line `(k) the terms and conditions for optimal utilisation of spectrum under sub-section (1) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(l) the period of unutilised spectrum for insufficient reasons and further terms and conditions`
  line `relating to spectrum utilisation under sub-section (2) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(m) the terms and conditions, including applicable fees or charges for sharing, trading, leasing`
  line `and surrender of assigned spectrum, under sub-section (2) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(n) ) the timeline for granting permission for right of way for telecommunication network in`
  line `public property; and the amount for administrative expenses and compensation for right of way under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(o) the procedure to be followed by a facility provider to enter, survey, establish, operate,`
  line `maintain, repair, replace or relocate the telecommunication network, including the notice period, the manner of issuance of notice, the framework governing objections by owner or occupier of the`
  line `property, the manner in which such objections would be resolved, and matters relating to the`
  line `compensation payable for any damage under sub-section (5) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(p) the terms and conditions, including charges for right of way, and compensation for damage to`
  line `the property, under sub-section (6) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(q) the terms and conditions, including fees and charges subject to which the telecommunication`
  line `network to be made available on open access basis to facility providers under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 15;`
  line
  line `(r) the procedure and manner for giving prior notice under sub-section (1) of section 17;`
  line
  line `(s) the timeline for responding the notice with details of telecommunication network and`
  line `precautionary measures to be undertaken by the facility provider under sub-section (2) of section 17;`
  line
  line `(t) the procedure and safeguards for public emergency or public safety under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 20;`
  line
  line `(u) the duration and manner of taking action for public emergency or public safety under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(v) the measures to protect and ensure cyber security of, telecommunication networks and`
  line `telecommunication services under sub-section (1) of section 22;`
  line
  line `(w) the standards, security practices, upgradation requirements and procedures to be implemented`
  line `for the Critical Telecommunication Infrastructure under sub-section (4) of section 22;`
  line
  line `(x) the manner for administration of Digital Bharat Nidhi under section 26;`
  line
  line `(y) the manner and duration for creating Regulatory Sandbox under section 27;`
  line
  line `(z) the measures for protection of users under sub-section (2) of section 28;`
  line
  line `(za) the manner for registration of any grievance and redressal of such grievances pertaining to`
  line `the telecommunication service under sub-section (3) of section 28;`
  line
  line `(zb) the terms and conditions for participating in the dispute resolution mechanism under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 30;`
  line
  line `(zc) the form, manner and fees to be accompanied with the complaint under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 33;`
  line
  line `(zd) the manner for holding inquiry by the Adjudicating Officer under sub-section (1) of section`
  line 35;
  line
  line `(ze) the form, manner and fees for filing an appeal before the Designated Appeals Committee`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 36;`
  line
  line `(zf) the techno-legal measures for functioning of the Adjudicating Officer and the Designated`
  line `Appeals Committee under sub-section (1) of section 37;`
  line
  line `(zg) the terms and conditions of security interest under section 45;`
  line
  line `(zh) the terms and conditions, including applicable fees and charges for granting certificates under`
  line `section 46;`
  line
  line `(zi) the manner of certification, qualification, and terms and conditions, including fees and`
  line `charges for the examination for amateur station operator under section 47;`
  line
  line `(zj) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed, or in respect of which provision is to`
  line `be made by rules.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act and amendment to the Schedule made under section 57 shall be`
  line `laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total`
  line `period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and`
  line `if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid,`
  line `both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or amendment to the Schedule or both Houses`
  line `agree that the rule or amendment to the Schedule should not be made, the rule or amendment to the`
  line `Schedule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so,`
  line `however, any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything`
  line `previously done under that rule or amendment to the Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (91771)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Power of Central Government to amend Schedules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91771&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this`
  line `section, the Central Government may, by notification, —`
  line
  line `(a) amend the First Schedule;`
  line
  line `(b) amend the Second Schedule or the Third Schedule:`
  line
  line `Provided that penalty or civil penalty specified in such Schedules shall be not exceeding ten crore`
  line rupees.
  line
  line `(2) Any amendment made under sub-section (1) shall have effect as if enacted in this Act and shall`
  line `come into force on the date of the notification, unless the notification otherwise direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (91772)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91772&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions,`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as may be necessary or expedient, for removing the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiration of three years from the`
  line `date of commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (91773)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Amendment to Act 24 of 1997.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91773&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `In the Telecom Regulatory Authority of India Act, 1997, ---`
  line
  line `(a) in section 2, ---`
  line
  line `(i) in sub-section (1),---`
  line
  line `(A) for clause (e), the following clause shall be substituted, namely:---`
  line
  line `'(e) "licensee" means an authorised entity providing telecommunication services`
  line `under the Telecommunications Act, 2023, or registered for providing cable television`
  line `network under the Cable Television Networks (Regulation) Act, 1995 (7 of 1995) or any`
  line `other Act for the time being in force;';`
  line
  line `(B) for clause (ea), the following clause shall be substituted, namely:---`
  line
  line `'(ea) "licensor" means the Central Government which grants an authorisation for`
  line `telecommunication services under the Telecommunications Act, 2023, or registration`
  line `under the Cable Television Networks (Regulation) Act, 1995 (7 of 1995) or any other`
  line `Act for the time being in force;';`
  line
  line `(C) after clause (j), the following clause shall be inserted, namely: ---`
  line
  line `'(ja) "telecommunication" shall have the meaning as assigned to it in the`
  line `Telecommunications Act, 2023;---;`
  line
  line `(D) for clause (k), the following clause shall be substituted, namely:---`
  line
  line `'(k) "telecommunication services" means any service for telecommunication;";`
  line
  line `(ii) in sub-section (2), for the words and figures "the Indian Telegraph Act, 1885 (13 of 1885)`
  line `or the Indian Wireless Telegraphy Act, 1933 (17 of 1933)", the words, figures and brackets "the`
  line `Telecommunications Act, 2023 or the Cable Television Networks (Regulation) Act, 1995 (7 of`
  line `1995)" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(b) in section 4, for the proviso, the following provisos shall be substituted, namely:---`
  line
  line `"Provided that a person who is, or has been, in the service of Government shall not be`
  line `appointed"`
  line
  line `(a) as a Chairperson unless such person has held the post of Secretary to the Government`
  line `of India or any equivalent post in the Central Government or the State Government; or`
  line
  line `(b) as a member unless such person has held the post of Additional Secretary to the`
  line `Government of India or any equivalent post in the Central Government or the State`
  line `Government:`
  line
  line `Provided further that a person who is, or has been, in a service other than that of Government,`
  line `shall be appointed--`
  line
  line `(a) as a Chairperson if such person has at least thirty years of professional experience and`
  line `has served as a member of the board of directors or a chief executive of a company in the`
  line `areas as specified in this section; or`
  line
  line `(b) as a Member if such person has at least twenty-five years of professional experience`
  line `and has served as a member of the board of directors or chief executive of a company in the`
  line `areas as specified in this section.";`
  line
  line `(c) in section 11,---`
  line
  line `(i) in sub-section (1), --`
  line
  line `(A) for the words and figures "Indian Telegraph Act, 1885 (13 of 1885)", the words,`
  line `figures and brackets "Telecommunications Act, 2023 or the Cable Television Networks`
  line `(Regulation) Act, 1995 (7 of 1995)" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(B) in the fifth proviso, for the portion beginning with the words may, within fifteen`
  line `days from the date of receipt and ending with the words take a final decision, the`
  line `following shall be substituted, namely:---`
  line
  line `shall, within thirty days from the date of receipt of such reference communicate to the`
  line `Central Government any further recommendations that it may have, after considering the`
  line `reference made by the Central Government and after receipt of further recommendation if`
  line `any, the Central Government shall take a final decision.`
  line `';`
  line
  line `(ii) in sub-section (2),---`
  line
  line `(A) for the words and figures Indian Telegraph Act, 1885 (13 of 1885)", the words, figures`
  line `and brackets "Telecommunications Act, 2023 or the Cable Television Networks (Regulation)`
  line `Act, 1995 (7 of 1995)" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(B) after the proviso, the following proviso shall be inserted, namely:---`
  line
  line `"Provided further that the Authority may direct an authorised entity or class of authorised`
  line `entities providing telecommunication services, to abstain from predatory pricing that is`
  line `harmful to competition, long term development and the overall health of the`
  line `telecommunication sector.";`
  line
  line `(d) in section 14, in clause (a),---`
  line
  line `(i) sub-clause (i) shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(ii) for paragraph (C), the following shall be substituted, namely:---`
  line
  line `"(C) any disputes to be adjudicated by the Adjudicating Officer or the Designated`
  line `Appeals Committee under the Telecommunications Act, 2023;`
  line
  line `(iii) after clause (c), the following clause shall be inserted, namely:---`
  line
  line `"(d) hear and dispose of appeals under section 39 of the Telecommunications Act, 2023.`
  line
  line `Any action instituted under the Telecom Regulatory Authority of India Act, 1997`
  line `(24 of 1997) and pending immediately before the appointed day in the Telecom Disputes`
  line `Settlement and Appellate Tribunal, shall continue to be heard and disposed of by the Telecom`
  line `Disputes Settlement and Appellate Tribunal as if this Act had not been passed;";`
  line
  line `(e) for section 38, the following section shall be substituted, namely:---`
  line
  line `"38. Application of certain laws.--- The provisions of this Act shall be in addition to the`
  line `provisions of the Telecommunications Act, 2023 and, in particular, nothing in this Act shall affect`
  line `any jurisdiction, powers and functions required to be exercised or performed by the appropriate`
  line `authority in relation to any area falling within the jurisdiction of such authority."`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (91774)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Repeal of certain Acts and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91774&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the other provisions of this section, the`
  line `enactments namely, the Indian Telegraph Act, 1885 (13 of 1885), and the Indian Wireless Telegraphy`
  line `Act, 1933 (17 of 1933), are hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the repeal of the provisions aforesaid, anything done or any action taken`
  line `including any grant of license, registration or assignment, any order, or proceeding, pending or ongoing,`
  line `under the repealed provisions shall be deemed to have been done or taken under this Act, and the`
  line `provisions of this Act shall have effect in relation thereto.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of Part-III of the Indian Telegraph Act, 1885 (13 of 1885) shall continue to apply`
  line `to all cases pertaining to laying down of transmission lines under section 164 of the Electricity Act, 2003`
  line `(36 of 2003) as if the Indian Telegraph Act, 1885 has not been repealed, and the provisions of Part-III of`
  line `the Indian Telegraph Act, 1885 shall continue in force with reference to section 164 of the Electricity Act,`
  line `2003 till such time as section 164 of the Electricity Act, 2003 is amended.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (91775)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Existing rules to continue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91775&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `All rules, orders, made or purported to have been made under the`
  line `Indian Telegraph Act, 1885 (13 of 1885) or under the Indian Wireless Telegraphy Act, 1933 (17 of 1933),`
  line `shall, in so far as they relate to matters for which provision is made in this Act and are not inconsistent`
  line `therewith, be deemed to have been made under this Act as if this Act had been in force on the date on`
  line `which such rules, orders were made, and shall continue in force unless and until they are superseded by`
  line `any rules made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (91776)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Validation of certain acts and indemnity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853&sectionId=91776&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_58_00002_202344_1721027001853
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `All acts of executive actions done, decisions taken,`
  line `actions done, proceedings taken and orders passed, prior to the appointed day, by the Central`
  line `Government, by any officer of the Central Government, or by any other authority, with respect to`
  line `assignment of spectrum or provision of telecommunication services, or telecommunication network or`
  line `establishment of telecommunication infrastructure, in the belief or purported belief that the acts done,`
  line `decisions taken, actions done, and proceedings taken, were being done, taken or passed under the Indian`
  line `Telegraph Act, 1885 (13 of 1885), or the Indian Wireless Telegraphy Act, 1933 (17 of 1933), shall be as`
  line `valid and operative as if they had been done, taken or passed in accordance with law; and no suit or other legal proceeding shall be maintained or continued against any person whatsoever, on the ground that any`
  line `such acts, decisions, proceedings taken were not done or taken in accordance with law.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
